-- Polish Stocks: PBG, PKO Bank Polski, Synthos Are Active
-- B y   P i o t r   S k o l i m o w s k i
-- 2012-07-02T16:26:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-02/polish-stocks-pbg-pko-bank-polski-synthos-are-active.html
Poland’s  WIG20 Index (WIG20)  retreated 0.9
percent to 2,254.86 in Warsaw.  The following were among the most active stocks on the
 Warsaw Stock Exchange  today. Stock symbols follow company names.  PBG SA (PBG)   jumped 19 percent to 7.31 zloty, the most
since August 2004. The Polish construction company declared
bankrupt last month may ask a government fund for state aid to
resume operations, said Kinga Banaszak-Filipiak, a PBG
spokeswoman.  PKO Bank Polski SA (PKO)  , a state-owned lender, declined
2.5 percent to 33.75 zloty, the lowest level in a week. Poland’s
Treasury Ministry is considering selling minority stakes in
listed companies after it had to postpone initial public
offerings of Grupa PHN SA and PAK SA, Parkiet reported, citing a
banker it didn’t name.  Synthos SA (SNS)   jumped 3.9 percent to 6.16 zloty, the
most in three weeks. The Polish chemical producer owned by
billionaire Michal Solowow won’t increase its bid for state-
controlled fertilizer maker Zaklady Azotowe Pulawy SA above the
102.5 zloty a share it is offering until July 20, Chief
Executive Officer Tomasz Kalwat told Rzeczpospolita newspaper.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Piotr Skolimowski in Warsaw at 
